name: Snivy
flavorText: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: Servine
flavorText: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

attack.name: Wrap
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Serperior ex

abilities.name: Regal Cheer
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Pokémon do 20 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Command the Grass
attack.text: You may search your deck for up to 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Pansage
flavorText: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

attack.name: Collect
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Simisage
flavorText: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Petilil
flavorText: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

attack.name: Hide
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Lilligant
flavorText: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

attack.name: Bemusing Aroma
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned. If tails, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Maractus
flavorText: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

attack.name: Lively Needles
attack.text: If this Pokémon was healed during this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Karrablast

abilities.name: Stimulated Evolution
abilities.text: If you have Shelmet in play, this Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

flavorText: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: Foongus
flavorText: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

attack.name: Toxic Spore
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

attack.name: Dangerous Reaction
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

attack.name: V-Force
attack.text: If you have 4 or fewer Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.

name: Darumaka
flavorText: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: Darmanitan
flavorText: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

attack.name: Searing Flame
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attack.name: Smashing Headbutt
attack.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Larvesta
flavorText: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

attack.name: Peck Off
attack.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Volcarona

abilities.name: Torrid Scales
abilities.text: You must discard a Basic {R} Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may make your opponent’s Active Pokémon Burned.

flavorText: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

attack.text: You must discard a Basic Fire Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may make your opponent’s Active Pokémon Burned.

name: Panpour
flavorText: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

attack.name: Collect
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Simipour
flavorText: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Tympole
flavorText: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

attack.name: Round
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Palpitoad
flavorText: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

attack.name: Round
attack.text: This attack does 40 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Seismitoad
flavorText: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

attack.name: Round
attack.text: This attack does 70 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Tirtouga
flavorText: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

attack.name: Ancient Seaweed
attack.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Item card in your opponent’s discard pile.

name: Carracosta

abilities.name: Mighty Shell
abilities.text: Prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon by your opponent’s Pokémon that have any Special Energy attached.

flavorText: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

attack.name: Big Bite
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Alomomola

abilities.name: Gentle Fin
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may put a Basic Pokémon with 70 HP or less from your discard pile onto your Bench.

flavorText: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: Cubchoo
flavorText: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

attack.name: Snotted Up
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Beartic
flavorText: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

attack.name: Continuous Headbutt
attack.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

attack.name: Sheer Cold
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

attack.name: Drag Off
attack.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. This attack does 20 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Kyurem ex

attack.name: Blizzard Burst
attack.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon for each Prize card your opponent has taken. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Emolga
flavorText: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

attack.name: Call for Family
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

attack.name: Hold Still
attack.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Eelektrik

abilities.name: Dynamotor
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic {L} Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

attack.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

attack.name: Thunder Fang
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attack.name: Buzz Flip
attack.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

attack.name: Charge
attack.text: Search your deck for a Basic Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Disaster Volt
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Zekrom ex

attack.name: Voltage Burst
attack.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken. This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Munna
flavorText: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

attack.name: Rest
attack.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. Heal 30 damage from it.

name: Musharna
flavorText: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

attack.name: Dream Calling
attack.text: You may search your deck for any number of Fennel cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Sleep Pulse
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

attack.name: Cellular Evolution
attack.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

attack.name: Cellular Ascension
attack.text: For each of your Benched Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Evo-Lariat
attack.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each of your Evolution Pokémon in play.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

attack.name: Slight Shift
attack.text: Move an Energy from 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon to another of their Pokémon.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

attack.name: Calm Mind
attack.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

attack.name: Psychic
attack.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Golett
flavorText: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

attack.name: Best Punch
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

attack.name: Double Smash
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Meloetta ex

abilities.name: Debut Performance
abilities.text: If you go first, this Pokémon can use attacks during your first turn.

attack.name: Echoed Voice
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon’s Echoed Voice attack does 80 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Excadrill ex

attack.name: Piercing Drill
attack.text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attack.name: Rock Tumble
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Resistance.

name: Timburr
flavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
flavorText: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

attack.name: Hammer Arm
attack.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

name: Conkeldurr

abilities.name: Craftsmanship
abilities.text: This Pokémon gets +40 HP for each {F} Energy attached to it.

flavorText: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

attack.text: This Pokémon gets +40 HP for each Fighting Energy attached to it.

attack.name: Swing Around
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

name: Throh
flavorText: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

attack.name: Shoulder Throw
attack.text: This attack does 30 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s Retreat Cost.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

attack.name: Flail
attack.text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Crustle

abilities.name: Sturdy
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, it is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

flavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

attack.name: Stone Edge
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Landorus
flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

attack.name: Abundant Harvest
attack.text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Earthquake
attack.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Venipede
flavorText: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

attack.name: Poison Spray
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Whirlipede
flavorText: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

attack.name: Venoshock
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Scolipede

abilities.name: Poison Point
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

attack.name: Venoshock
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Sandile
flavorText: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards a card from their hand.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.

attack.name: Cursed Slug
attack.text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Escavalier
flavorText: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

attack.name: Wild Lances
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

attack.name: Hard Gears
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Klang
flavorText: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

attack.name: Hard Gears
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Klinklang

abilities.name: Gear Coating
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon that have any {M} Energy attached take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

attack.text: All of your Pokémon that have any Metal Energy attached take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

attack.name: Corner
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

attack.name: Finishing Blow
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

attack.name: Righteous Edge
attack.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Metal Arms
attack.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 40 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Genesect ex

abilities.name: Metallic Signal
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Evolution {M} Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Evolution Metal Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Protect Charge
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Axew
flavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

attack.name: Gather Strength
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

attack.name: Boundless Power
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

attack.name: Cross-Cut
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 80 more damage.

attack.name: Axe Blast
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it is Knocked Out.

name: Pidove
flavorText: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

attack.name: Scout
attack.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Tranquill
flavorText: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

attack.name: Fly
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

attack.name: Add On
attack.text: Draw 4 cards.

attack.name: Swift Flight
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Audino
flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

attack.name: Return
attack.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Minccino
flavorText: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

attack.name: Tail Slap
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

attack.name: Do the Wave
attack.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Rufflet
flavorText: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: Braviary
flavorText: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

attack.name: Aerial Ace
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon Tool rule: You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
name: Air Balloon

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: The Retreat Cost of the Pokémon this card is attached to is ColorlessColorless less.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Antique Cover Fossil

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text:
Play this card as if it were a 60-HP Basic Colorless Pokémon. This card can’t be affected by any Special Conditions and can’t retreat. At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play. Ability ⇢ Protective Cover
Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent’s Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Energy Coin

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, search your deck for a Basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Fennel

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Heal 40 damage from each of your Pokémon.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: N’s Plan

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Move up to 2 Energy from your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Pokégear 3.0

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal a Supporter card you find there and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Professor’s Research

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy. If this card is attached to a Basic Pokémon, this card provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time.

name: Cubchoo

attack.name: Snotted Up
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Beartic
flavorText: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

attack.name: Continuous Headbutt
attack.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

attack.name: Sheer Cold
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

attack.name: Drag Off
attack.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. This attack does 20 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

name: Emolga
flavorText: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

attack.name: Call for Family
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

attack.name: Hold Still
attack.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Eelektrik

abilities.name: Dynamotor
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic {L} Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

attack.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Lightning Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

attack.name: Thunder Fang
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attack.name: Buzz Flip
attack.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Munna
flavorText: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

attack.name: Rest
attack.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. Heal 30 damage from it.

name: Musharna
flavorText: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

attack.name: Dream Calling
attack.text: You may search your deck for any number of Fennel cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Sleep Pulse
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Solosis
flavorText: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

attack.name: Cellular Evolution
attack.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

attack.name: Slight Shift
attack.text: Move an Energy from 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon to another of their Pokémon.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

attack.name: Calm Mind
attack.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

attack.name: Psychic
attack.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Golett
flavorText: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

attack.name: Best Punch
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Golurk
flavorText: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

attack.name: Double Smash
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: Timburr
flavorText: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: Gurdurr
flavorText: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

attack.name: Hammer Arm
attack.text: Discard the top card of your opponent’s deck.

name: Conkeldurr

abilities.name: Craftsmanship
abilities.text: This Pokémon gets +40 HP for each {F} Energy attached to it.

flavorText: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

attack.text: This Pokémon gets +40 HP for each Fighting Energy attached to it.

attack.name: Swing Around
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

name: Throh
flavorText: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

attack.name: Shoulder Throw
attack.text: This attack does 30 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s Retreat Cost.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

attack.name: Flail
attack.text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Crustle

abilities.name: Sturdy
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, it is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

flavorText: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

attack.name: Stone Edge
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Landorus
flavorText: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

attack.name: Abundant Harvest
attack.text: Attach a Basic Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Earthquake
attack.text: This attack also does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Venipede
flavorText: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

attack.name: Poison Spray
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Whirlipede
flavorText: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

attack.name: Venoshock
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Scolipede

abilities.name: Poison Point
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

attack.name: Venoshock
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Sandile
flavorText: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards a card from their hand.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

attack.name: Tighten Up
attack.text: Your opponent discards 2 cards from their hand.

attack.name: Cursed Slug
attack.text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Escavalier
flavorText: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

attack.name: Wild Lances
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

attack.name: Hard Gears
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Klang
flavorText: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

attack.name: Hard Gears
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Klinklang

abilities.name: Gear Coating
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon that have any {M} Energy attached take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

attack.text: All of your Pokémon that have any Metal Energy attached take 20 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Pawniard
flavorText: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

attack.name: Corner
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

attack.name: Finishing Blow
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

attack.name: Righteous Edge
attack.text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Metal Arms
attack.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Axew
flavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

attack.name: Gather Strength
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

attack.name: Boundless Power
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Haxorus
flavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

attack.name: Cross-Cut
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 80 more damage.

attack.name: Axe Blast
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it is Knocked Out.

name: Pidove
flavorText: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

attack.name: Scout
attack.text: Your opponent reveals their hand.

name: Tranquill
flavorText: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

attack.name: Fly
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

attack.name: Add On
attack.text: Draw 4 cards.

attack.name: Swift Flight
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Audino
flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

attack.name: Return
attack.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Minccino
flavorText: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

attack.name: Tail Slap
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

attack.name: Do the Wave
attack.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Rufflet
flavorText: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: Braviary
flavorText: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

attack.name: Aerial Ace
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon’s Echoed Voice attack does 80 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Excadrill ex

attack.text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attack.name: Rock Tumble
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Resistance.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

attack.name: V-Force
attack.text: If you have 4 or fewer Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.
